{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T13:58:11.135Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files are the primary mechanism for giving Claude Code persistent, cross-session instructions. They are plain Markdown files you author and place in specific locations in your filesystem, and Claude reads them automatically at the start of every session — functioning as the \"long-term memory\" that survives the otherwise fresh context window of each new conversation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What CLAUDE.md Files Are"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every Claude Code session starts with an empty context window. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files solve the problem of re-explaining the same project context, conventions, and rules in every session. You write them once in plain Markdown; Claude reads them at launch and treats their contents as persistent instructions for the duration of the session. They are distinct from Claude's "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"auto memory"},{"type":"text","text":" (notes Claude writes itself), and from settings files, which enforce hard rules through the client."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Two Memory Systems Side-by-Side"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude Code provides two complementary memory mechanisms, both loaded at session start:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md Files"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auto Memory"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Who writes it"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What it contains"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instructions and rules"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Learnings and patterns"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Scope"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Project, user, or org"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Per repository, shared across worktrees"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Load limit"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Full file (always)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"First 200 lines or 25KB of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"MEMORY.md"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use for"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coding standards, architecture, workflows"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build commands, debugging insights, discovered preferences"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CLAUDE.md is for guidance you consciously author. Auto memory is Claude's equivalent of a personal notebook — it writes to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/projects/<project>/memory/MEMORY.md"},{"type":"text","text":" as it learns from your corrections and habits across sessions."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where to Place CLAUDE.md Files"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CLAUDE.md files are scope-aware. Claude walks up the directory tree from the working directory and loads all "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files it discovers, concatenating them in order from filesystem root to project root — more specific files are read "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"last"},{"type":"text","text":", giving them higher contextual weight."}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scope"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Location"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared with"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Managed/Org policy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/etc/claude-code/CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" (Linux) or OS equivalent"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All users on the machine"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"User (all projects)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/CLAUDE.md"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Just you, across all projects"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Project (team)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"./CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"./.claude/CLAUDE.md"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Team via source control"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local (private)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"./CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":" (add to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".gitignore"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Just you, current project only"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Files in subdirectories "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"below"},{"type":"text","text":" the working directory are loaded on demand — only when Claude reads files in that subdirectory — rather than at launch."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Bootstrap: The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/init"},{"type":"text","text":" Command"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rather than writing a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" from scratch, running "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/init"},{"type":"text","text":" in your project directory causes Claude to analyze your codebase and generate a starter file automatically, including build and test commands and any conventions it can infer. If a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" already exists, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/init"},{"type":"text","text":" suggests improvements instead of overwriting it. With the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE_CODE_NEW_INIT=1"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable set, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/init"},{"type":"text","text":" runs an interactive multi-phase flow: it explores your codebase via a subagent, asks follow-up questions to fill gaps, and presents a reviewable proposal before writing any files."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Writing Effective Instructions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Because "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" content is injected into the context window as a user message (not the system prompt), Claude treats it as strong guidance — not hard enforcement. Vague instructions are followed inconsistently. The practical guidelines are:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Target under 200 lines per file."},{"type":"text","text":" Longer files consume more context tokens and reduce adherence. If your instructions grow beyond this, move specific sections into path-scoped rules."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Be concrete and verifiable."},{"type":"text","text":" Write "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"\"Use 2-space indentation\""},{"type":"text","text":" rather than "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"\"Format code properly\""},{"type":"text","text":". Write "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"\"Run npm test before committing\""},{"type":"text","text":" rather than "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"\"Test your changes\""},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Markdown structure."},{"type":"text","text":" Headers and bullets help Claude scan the file the same way a human reader would — organized sections outperform dense paragraphs."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Eliminate contradictions."},{"type":"text","text":" If two rules conflict (across nested "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" files or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/"},{"type":"text","text":"), Claude may pick one arbitrarily. Review files periodically to remove stale or conflicting entries."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Importing Other Files"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" file can pull in additional content using "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"@path/to/file"},{"type":"text","text":" syntax:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"markdown"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"See @README for project overview and @package.json for available npm commands.\n\n# Additional Instructions\n- Git workflow: @docs/git-instructions.md"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both relative and absolute paths are supported. Imported files are expanded and injected into context at launch — they do "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"not"},{"type":"text","text":" reduce your context window usage, they just help with organization. Recursive imports are supported up to four levels deep. Wrapping a path in backticks prevents importing: `"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"@README"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"` is treated as literal text."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Path-Scoped Rules in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For large projects, you can move topic-specific instructions out of a monolithic "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" and into "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/"},{"type":"text","text":" — a directory of modular Markdown files:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"your-project/\n├── .claude/\n│   ├── CLAUDE.md\n│   └── rules/\n│       ├── code-style.md\n│       ├── testing.md\n│       └── security.md"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rules without frontmatter load at every session. Rules with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"paths"},{"type":"text","text":" frontmatter load "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"conditionally"},{"type":"text","text":" — only when Claude reads files matching the specified glob patterns:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"markdown"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\npaths:\n  - \"src/api/**/*.ts\"\n---\n\n# API Development Rules\n- All API endpoints must include input validation\n- Use the standard error response format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the primary mechanism for keeping context lean on large codebases: TypeScript API rules only appear in context when Claude is working with TypeScript API files, not during every session regardless of task."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/memory"},{"type":"text","text":" Command"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Running "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/memory"},{"type":"text","text":" inside any session gives you a live view of all "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.local.md"},{"type":"text","text":", and rules files currently loaded in that session. It also provides a toggle for auto memory and a link to open the auto memory folder. This is the primary debugging tool when Claude appears to be ignoring your instructions — if a file isn't listed in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/memory"},{"type":"text","text":", Claude cannot see it."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"AGENTS.md Interoperability"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"If your repository already uses an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"AGENTS.md"},{"type":"text","text":" file for other AI coding agents (like Codex), Claude Code reads "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" — not "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"AGENTS.md"},{"type":"text","text":". To avoid duplicating instructions, create a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" that imports "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"AGENTS.md"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"markdown"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"@AGENTS.md\n\n## Claude Code\nUse plan mode for changes under `src/billing/`."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Running "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/init"},{"type":"text","text":" in a repo that has an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"AGENTS.md"},{"type":"text","text":" will read it and incorporate its relevant parts into the generated "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" automatically."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" is the authoritative human-authored memory layer in Claude Code — write it for anything you'd otherwise re-explain each session."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Four scope levels exist: managed policy → user → project → local. All matching files in the directory tree are concatenated, with more specific files taking precedence."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instructions are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"context"},{"type":"text","text":", not enforcement. For hard enforcement (e.g., blocking commands), use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"permissions.deny"},{"type":"text","text":" in settings or PreToolUse hooks instead."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep individual files under 200 lines for best adherence; use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/rules/"},{"type":"text","text":" with path frontmatter to scope instructions to relevant file types only."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/init"},{"type":"text","text":" to auto-generate a starter file and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/memory"},{"type":"text","text":" to audit what's currently loaded in your session."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto memory ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"MEMORY.md"},{"type":"text","text":") is Claude's counterpart — it writes its own notes across sessions, while "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"CLAUDE.md"},{"type":"text","text":" is what you write for Claude."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
